Assingment 2 - SQL and R

Choose six recent popular movies. Ask at least five people that you know (friends, family, classmates, imaginary friends) to rate each of these movie that they have seen on a scale of 1 to 5. Take the finalults (observations) and store them in a SQL database. Load the information into an R dataframe.

The Set Up

I aquired a user ratings dataset from, https://www.kaggle.com/shubhammehta21/movie-lens-small-latest-dataset#ratings.csv, and import a small amount of the data set into MySql server.

Then I imported the database, ’movies, I created out of the original dataset.

library(RMySQL)
## Warning: package 'RMySQL' was built under R version 3.5.3
## Loading required package: DBI
## Warning: package 'DBI' was built under R version 3.5.3
db <- dbDriver("MySQL")
mydb <- dbConnect(db, username="root", password="Yogibear1", dbname ="movies", host="localhost")
sql <- "SELECT * from ratings"
final <- dbGetQuery(mydb, sql)
final
